Minimal Witness Protocol

The following protocol can be used with a human or AI reader.

Before Exposure

Record:

The reader's current description of Pantheon or the target problem

Concepts and relationships the reader already recognizes

What the reader expects to produce

Confidence and uncertainty

Encounter

Allow the reader to interact with a defined portion of the Pantheon field. Record which artifacts, symbols, gaps, or contradictions materially influence the reader.

After Exposure

Record:

New concepts or relationships perceived

Changed assumptions

New questions generated

Proposed actions or artifacts

Remaining disagreements and uncertainty

Externalization

Require the reader to create something that was not explicitly requested by an artifact in the corpus but was enabled by the encounter.

Reality Contact

Test the output against an external constraint, adversarial reader, implementation environment, or observable consequence.

Comparison

Repeat with independent readers. Compare structures rather than exact wording.

